#3401
Choose Your Race~
   Since all beings are created with a gender, you are urged by Kelemvor's
servants here to select the race you would choose for your being during your
life on Toril.  It is said that the Gods allow some stalwart followers of their
to reincarnate as advanced races, and if you are one of these lucky fellows you
may ask any deity in the heavens above to change your race now, if indeed there
are any available for such a task.  However, if you are like most souls coming
through these gates, you must choose a common race.  But be not vexed for this,
as the common races, though plentiful, are as rich in culture and are by no
means left aside in the realm of ability either.  The ghostly servant escorting
you through your journey of creation explains to you that you may receive a
message to your mind of what races are avaialble through the @Ylistraces@n
command.  Once you are ready to choose a race, you simply must use the
@Ysetrace@n command followed by the name of the race you wish to become.  For
example: setrace icefolk barbarian.  This would set your race to that of the
icefolk barbarians common in the far reaches of the North such as Icewind Dale.
When you have chosen your race simply go north to continue your creation.  If
you need more information on a race, please use @Yhelp @Yrace @Y<racename>@n.  
