#3403
Choose Your Ability Scores~
   You are urged into this area by Kelemvor's servants to set your ability
scores.  You can do this by using the @Ysetstats@n command.  The proper syntax
is @Ysetstats @Y<ability @Yscore> @Y<new @Yscore>@n or @Ysetstats @Yshow@n to
display your stats.  For example, @Ysetstats @Ystrength @Y16@n would set your
strength to 16 if you had enough points to buy that score.  You start off with
20 stat points to assign, and the higher the stat the more points it costs.  
The available ability scores are strength, dexterity, constitution,
intelligence, wisdom and charisma.  Type @Yhelp @Yability @Yscore @Y<name>@n for
more information on each ability score.  
