#3408
Beginner's Lesson 3 - Doors~
   Sometimes exits are blocked with a door of some kind whether it be an actual
door, a sewer manhole, a gate, or what have you.  In order to open it, you must
type @Yopen @Y<door @Ykeyword>@n.  If it is locked and you have the key, you can
unlock it using the @Yunlock @Y<door @Ykeyword>@n command.  If you have the pick
locks skill practiced, you can pick the lock by typing @Ypick @Y<door
@Ykeyword>@n.  Sometimes exits are hidden and you are able to find them by using
the @Ysearch @Y<direction>@N command.  @n
