#3409
Beginner's Lesson 4 - Containers~
   You will often interact with containers such as bags and backpacks throughout
the game.  In order to get something from the container, whether it be a bag or
a corpse of the mob you just killed, you will need to type @Yget @Y<item
@Ykeyword> @Y<container @Ykeyword>@n.  For example, get coins corpse.  You can
also get all items from a container by typing @Yget @Yall @Y<container
@Ykeyword>@n.  If you want to put something in a container type @Yput @Y<item
@Ykeyword> @Y<container @Ykeyword>@n, and just like get, you can use the all
keyword in place of the item keyword to put everything in your inventory into a
container.  You can see what is typeing @Yinventory@n or just @Yi@n@N for short.

